<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Drip for Peanuts</span>
            <h2>Precision Peg-Zone Moisture for Premium Grades</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🥜</div>
                <h3>Aflatoxin Prevention</h3>
                <p>Aflatoxin contamination occurs when peanuts experience water stress during the 2-week kernel fill period (R7). SDI maintains consistent peg-zone moisture throughout this critical window, preventing the stress that triggers Aspergillus flavus colonization.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">📏</div>
                <h3>Kernel Fill Control</h3>
                <p>Even, consistent moisture during R5–R8 drives complete kernel fill and reduces the "pop" percentage at harvest. SDI growers typically see kernel fill ratings improve by 8–12% vs. center pivot irrigated fields.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🚜</div>
                <h3>Harvest Timing Precision</h3>
                <p>Accurate pod maturity assessment requires consistent moisture leading up to harvest. SDI's controlled final irrigations provide the uniform soil moisture needed to accurately read pod color change and time digging.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌱</div>
                <h3>Calcium to the Peg Zone</h3>
                <p>Peanut peg calcium uptake is local — pods absorb calcium directly from the soil at the peg zone, not from roots. SDI can be used to deliver calcium solutions directly to this zone for improved pod quality.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌡️</div>
                <h3>Heat Stress Mitigation</h3>
                <p>The 2-week window from R7 to digging is also peak summer heat in Georgia, Texas, and Virginia peanut country. SDI maintains evaporative cooling and root-zone temperatures during this critical quality window.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-card">
                <div class="highlight-card-icon">📊</div>
                <h3>Case Study: SW Georgia</h3>
                <p>A 1,400-acre Virginia-type peanut operation converted from center pivot to SDI. Three-year average yield improved from 4,100 to 4,460 lbs/acre and aflatoxin rejections dropped from 6% to 0.8% of loads.</p>
                <a href="/growers-stories" class="btn-primary-sm" style="margin-top:16px;">Read Case Studies →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

