                <span class="section-eyebrow">System Design</span>
                <h2>Peanut SDI Design Considerations</h2>
                <p>Peanut SDI requires careful placement to deliver moisture to the peg zone without interfering with digging operations:</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li>Lateral spacing: 36 inches between twin-row beds</li>
                    <li>Installation depth: 8–12 inches (above typical digging depth)</li>
                    <li>Emitter spacing: 8–12 inches for loamy sand/sandy loam soils</li>
                    <li>System designed around 0.20–0.30 inches/day capacity</li>
                    <li>Calcium chloride fertigation compatibility built in</li>
                    <li>Anti-siphon emitters essential in sandy soils with rapid infiltration</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Talk to a Dealer</a>
